  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Apach HIV /AIDS Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims at tackling the spread of HIV/AIDS in Apach distirct of Lango subregion, northern Uganda, addressing stigmatisation and segregation of people affected by HIV/AIDS and providing income generating activities for those affected by the virus. This will be achieved by providing home-based care services to those bed-ridden and house-bound, increasing HIV/AIDS awareness, sexual health education, advocacy around issues of access rights, basic human rights, stigma and discrimination, gender equity; provision of practical assistance to orphans and widows; and strengthening the capacity of local groups and the two partner organisations with running costs, management skills training, planning and monitoring/evaluation. This will result in people living with HIV/AIDS and those affected by it as well as disabled to live dignified and hopeful lives and participating in their communities as equals and productive members. Apach district is in a very remote part of Lango and there has not been enoug HIV/AIDS intervention work in the district. The district has only one HIV testing centre at Apach town which many villagers can not access due to transportation problems. This project will aim to work with the health authorities to provide mobile HIV testing centres to the villages.</narrative>
  </description>
